label: Access URI
rdfs_comment: A URI that uniquely identifies a service that provides a representation of the underlying resource. If this resource can be acquired by an http request, its http URL should be given. If not, but it has some URI in another URI scheme, that may be given here.

label: Associated Observation Reference
rdfs_comment: A reference to an observation associated with this resource.

label: Associated Specimen Reference
rdfs_comment: A reference to a specimen associated with this resource.

label: Attribution Link URL
rdfs_comment: The URL where information about ownership, attribution, etc. of the resource may be found.

label: Attribution URL
rdfs_comment: The URL of the icon or logo image to appear in source attribution.

label: Caption
rdfs_comment: As alternative or in addition to description, a caption is free-form text to be displayed together with (rather than instead of) a resource that is suitable for captions (especially images).

label: Capture Device
rdfs_comment: Free form text describing the device or devices used to create the resource.

label: Commenter
rdfs_comment: A URI denoting a person, using some controlled vocabulary such as FOAF. Implementers and communities of practice may produce restrictions or recommendations on the choice of vocabularies.

label: Commenter
rdfs_comment: A name or the literal "anonymous" (= anonymously commented).

label: Comments
rdfs_comment: Any comment provided on the media resource, as free-form text. Best practice would also identify the commenter.

label: Derived From
rdfs_comment: A reference to an original resource from which the current one is derived.

label: Date and Time Digitized
rdfs_comment: Date the first digital version was created, if different from Original Date and Time found in the Temporal Coverage Vocabulary. The date and time must comply with the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) datetime practice, which requires that date and time representation correspond to ISO 8601:1998, but with year fields always comprising 4 digits. This makes datetime records compliant with 8601:2004. AC datetime values may also follow 8601:2004 for ranges by separating two IS0 8601 datetime fields by a solidus ("forward slash", '/'). See also the wikipedia IS0 8601 entry for further explanation and examples.

label: Funding
rdfs_comment: Organizations or individuals who funded the creation of the resource.

label: Further Information URL
rdfs_comment: The URL of a Web site that provides additional information about the version of the media resource that is provided by the Service Access Point.

label: Hash Function
rdfs_comment: The cryptographic hash function used to compute the value given in the Hash Value.

label: Hash
rdfs_comment: The value computed by a hash function applied to the media that will be delivered at the access point.

label: Service Access Point
rdfs_comment: In a chosen serialization (RDF, XML Schema, etc.) the potentially multiple service access points (e.g., for different resolutions of an image) might be provided in a referenced or in a nested object. This property identifies one such access point. That is, each of potentially multiple values of hasServiceAccessPoint identifies a set of representation-dependent metadata using the properties defined under the section Service Access Point Vocabulary.

label: ID of Containing Collection
rdfs_comment: If the resource is contained in a Collection, this field identifies that Collection uniquely. Its form is not specified by this normative document, but is left to implementers of specific implementations.

label: License Logo URL
rdfs_comment: A URL providing access to a logo that symbolizes the License.

label: Licensing Exception Statement
rdfs_comment: The licensing statement for this variant of the media resource if different from that given in the License Statement property of the resource.

label: Metadata Creator
rdfs_comment: Person or organization originally creating the resource metadata record.

label: Metadata Creator
rdfs_comment: Person or organization originally creating the resource metadata record.

label: Metadata Language
rdfs_comment: URI from the ISO639-2 list of URIs for ISO 3-letter language codes.

label: Metadata Language
rdfs_comment: Language of description and other metadata (but not necessarily of the image itself) represented as an ISO639-2 three letter language code. ISO639-1 two-letter codes are permitted but deprecated.

label: Metadata Provider
rdfs_comment: URI of person or organization originally responsible for providing the resource metadata record.

label: Metadata Provider
rdfs_comment: Person or organization originally responsible for providing the resource metadata record.

label: Other Scientific Name
rdfs_comment: One or several Scientific Taxon Names that are synonyms to the Scientific Taxon Name may be provided here.

label: Physical Setting
rdfs_comment: The setting of the content represented in media such as images, sounds, and movies if the provider deems them relevant. Constrained vocabulary of: "Natural" = Object in its natural setting of the object (e. g. living organisms in their natural environment); "Artificial" = Object in an artificial environment (e. g. living organisms in an artificial environment such as a zoo, garden, greenhouse, or laboratory); "Edited" = Human media editing of a natural setting or media acquisition with a separate media background such as a photographic backdrop.

label: Provider
rdfs_comment: URI for person or organization responsible for presenting the media resource. If no separate Metadata Provider is given, this also attributes the metadata.

label: Provider ID
rdfs_comment: A globally unique ID of the provider of the current AC metadata record.

label: Provider
rdfs_comment: Person or organization responsible for presenting the media resource. If no separate Metadata Provider is given, this also attributes the metadata.

label: Provider-managed ID
rdfs_comment: A free-form identifier (a simple number, an alphanumeric code, a URL, etc.) that is unique and meaningful primarily for the data provider.

label: Related Resource ID
rdfs_comment: Resource related in ways not specified through a collection, e.g., before-after images; time-lapse series; different orientations/angles of view

label: Resource Creation Technique
rdfs_comment: Information about technical aspects of the creation and digitization process of the resource. This includes modification steps ("retouching") after the initial resource capture.

label: Reviewer
rdfs_comment: URI for a reviewer. If present, then resource is peer-reviewed, even if there are Reviewer Comments is absent or empty. Its presence tells whether an expert in the subject featured in the media has reviewed the media item or collection and approved its metadata description; must display a name or the literal "anonymous" (= anonymously reviewed).

label: Reviewer Comments
rdfs_comment: Any comment provided by a reviewer with expertise in the subject, as free-form text.

label: Reviewer
rdfs_comment: String providing the name of a reviewer. If present, then resource is peer-reviewed, even if Reviewer Comments is absent or empty. Its presence tells whether an expert in the subject featured in the media has reviewed the media item or collection and approved its metadata description; must display a name or the literal "anonymous" (= anonymously reviewed).

label: Service Expectation
rdfs_comment: A term that describes what service expectations users may have of the ac:accessURL. Recommended terms include online (denotes that the URL is expected to deliver the resource), authenticate (denotes that the URL delivers a login or other authentication interface requiring completion before delivery of the resource) published(non digital) (denotes that the URL is the identifier of a non-digital published work, for example a doi.) Communities should develop their own controlled vocabularies for Service Expectations.

label: Subject Category Vocabulary
rdfs_comment: Any vocabulary or formal classification from which terms in the Subject Category have been drawn.

label: Subject Orientation
rdfs_comment: Specific orientation (= direction, view angle) of the subject represented in the media resource with respect to the acquisition device.

label: Subject Part
rdfs_comment: The portion or product of organism morphology, behaviour, environment, etc. that is either predominantly shown or particularly well exemplified by the media resource.

label: Subtype
rdfs_comment: Any URI may be used that provides for more specialization than the type. Possible values are community-defined. For exmamples see the non-normative page AC_Subtype_Examples.

label: Subtype
rdfs_comment: The subtype should provide more specialization than the type. Possible values are community-defined. For exmamples see the non-normative page AC_Subtype_Examples.

label: Tag
rdfs_comment: General keywords or tags.

label: Taxon Count
rdfs_comment: An exact or estimated number of taxa at the lowest applicable taxon rank (usually species or infraspecific) represented by the media resource (item or collection).

label: Taxon Coverage
rdfs_comment: A higher taxon (e. g., a genus, family, or order) at the level of the genus or higher, that covers all taxa that are the primary subject of the resource (which may be a media item or a collection).

label: Time of Day
rdfs_comment: Free text information beyond exact clock times.

label: Variant
rdfs_comment: A URI designating what this Service Access Point provides. Some suggested values are the URIs ac:Thumbnail, ac:Trailer, ac:LowerQuality, ac:MediumQuality, ac:GoodQuality, ac:BestQuality, and ac:Offline. Additional URIs from communities of practice may be introduced.

label: Variant Description
rdfs_comment: Text that describes this Service Access Point variant

label: Variant
rdfs_comment: Text that describes this Service Access Point variant.
